{"questionId":"12881","questionHtml":"<p>Use mathematical induction to prove that&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{2^{n + 1}} > {n^2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>n</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n \\in \\mathbb{Z}\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Z</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n \\geqslant 3\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>⩾</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>check for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n&nbsp;= 3\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span>,</p>\n<p>16&nbsp;&gt; 9 so true when&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n&nbsp;=&nbsp;3\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>assume true for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n&nbsp;= k\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>k</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{2^{k + 1}} > {k^2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>k</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M0</strong></em>&nbsp;for statements such as “let <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n&nbsp;= k\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>k</mi>\n</math></span>”.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Subsequent marks after this <em><strong>M1</strong></em> are independent of this mark and can be awarded.</p>\n<p>prove true for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n&nbsp;= k + 1\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{2^{k + 2}} = 2 \\times {2^{k + 1}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>k</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>k</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" > 2{k^2}\">\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = {k^2} + {k^2}\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" > {k^2} + 2k + 1\">\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span> (from part (a))&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; which is true for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k\">\n  <mi>k</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;≥ 3&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Only award the <em><strong>A1</strong></em> or the <em><strong>R1</strong></em> if it is clear why. Alternate methods are possible.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = {\\left( {K + 1} \\right)^2}\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>K</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>hence if true for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n&nbsp;= k\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>k</mi>\n</math></span> true for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n&nbsp;= k +1\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>, true for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n&nbsp;= 3\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span> so true for all <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;≥ 3&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Only award the final <em><strong>R1</strong></em> provided at least three of the previous marks are awarded.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12881","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ1.H_8b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Use mathematical induction to prove that 2 n + 1 > n 2 for n ∈ Z , n ⩾ 3 .","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Proof by induction, contradiction, counterexamples"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}